                      <b>Intolerant, hysterical and smug! How I hate the
                        organic fanatics<br>
                      </b>One net of four lemons - &pound;1.23; one net of
                      four ORGANIC lemons - &pound;2.49. One pint of
                      semi-skimmed milk - 89p; one pint of ORGANIC
                      semi-skimmed milk - &pound;1.20.<br>
                      These price differences incensed me so much the
                      other day that I spent an hour going round the
                      small supermarket in a town near my home in the
                      Cotswolds filling two trolleys with identical
                      items, one organic and 'eco-friendly', the other
                      non-organic and what you might call 'normal'.<br>
                      When I had filled my trolleys, I went into a
                      corner of the shop and worked out the cost of
                      each. The organic trolley was &pound;93.72. The other
                      &pound;66.30&#8230;<br>
                      See: <a
href="http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-1305566/Intolerant-hysterical-smug-How-I-hate-organic-fanatics.html#ixzz0xbHhSMS8">http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-1305566/<br>
