                    <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3"><br>
                      <b>An English Lesson<br>
                      </b><br>
                      For his 74th birthday, a man got a gift
                      certificate. <br>
                      &nbsp;<br>
                      The certificate paid for a visit to a medicine man
                      living on a nearby reservation who was rumored to
                      have a wonderful cure for erectile dysfunction.<br>
                      &nbsp;<br>
                      After being persuaded, he drove to the
                      reservation, handed his ticket to the medicine man
                      and wondered what was in store. <br>
                      <br>
                      The old man slowly, methodically produced a
                      potion, handed it to him, and with a grip on his
                      shoulder, warned, "This is powerful medicine and
                      it must be respected. <br>
                      <br>
                      You take only a teaspoonful and then say &#8216;1-2-3&#8217;.&nbsp;
                      &#8216;When you do that, you will become more manly than
                      you have ever been in your life and you can
                      perform as long as you want." <br>
                      &nbsp;<br>
                      The man was encouraged. As he walks away, he
                      turned and asked, "How do I stop the medicine from
                      working?" "Your partner must say '1-2-3-4,' he
                      responded. "But when she does, the medicine will
                      not work again until the next full moon." <br>
                      &nbsp;<br>
                      He was very eager to see if it worked so he went
                      home, showered, shaved, took a spoonful of the
                      medicine, and then invited his wife to join him in
                      the bedroom. <br>
                      &nbsp;<br>
                      When she came in, He took off his clothes and
                      said, &#8216;1-2-3!&#8217;<br>
                      Immediately, he was the manliest of men.<br>
                      &nbsp;<br>
                      His wife was excited and began throwing off her
                      clothes.<br>
                      And then she asked, &#8216;What was the 1-2-3 for?&#8217; <br>
                      &nbsp;<br>
                      And that, boys and girls, is why we should never
                      end our sentences with a preposition because we
                      could end up with a dangling participle.<br>
                      <br>
                    </font><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><br>
